 women's unique experiences and challenges their findings suggest that recent textbooks continue to propagate dominant gender norms within historical content and fall short of challenging or transforming gender relations about ice ice news contact information maps & directions ice news prof christine min wotipka and corbin schrader publish article in feminist formations february 21 2012 ice news history transformed gender in world war ii narratives in us history textbooks 1956 2007 carrie oelberger is pacs fellow in 2011 12 january 23 2012 ice doctoral student carrie oelberger is a fellow this year with stanford's center on philanthropy and civil society pacs brenda jarillo rabling awarded dissertation grant from aera january 23 2012 brenda jarillo rabling doctoral candidate in international comparative education received a dissertation grant from aera prof martin carnoy and brenda jarillo rabling publish two articles january 23 2012 professor carnoy and jarillo rabling publish articles in the higher education journal and the higher education quarterly alum piya sorcar named among world's top young innovators august 23 2011 school of education news sorcar receives honors for developing teachaids software to cut through taboos and educate about hiv stanford university school of education 485 lasuen mall stanford ca 94305 3096 tel 650 723 2109 copyright 2012 stanford university all rights reserved site map contact suse admissions helpsu maps & directions suse it axess academic calendar stanford bulletin office of the registrar edmail stanfordwho stanfordyou login connect with us connect with us on facebook connect with us on twitter connect with us on youtube connect with us on flickr website by lyudmila christie suse it
